    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-05-11T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-05-11T06:00:00-05:00" n="124"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d124">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89Yugoslavia/13: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Kingdom of the Serbs, Croats and
                        Slovenes</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dodge</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Belgrade</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-05-11T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 11, 1923—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received May 12—10:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6. In conferences with the Minister for Foreign Affairs and the Minister of
                    Finance I spoke to them in the sense of your telegram, No. 4, April 27, 6 p.m.
                    The matter was referred to a Cabinet council, and yesterday decision was taken
                    to send a mission to Washington in September or October next. The Minister of
                    Finance has informed me that unfortunately an earlier date is impossible as the
                    Parliamentary session is occupying all men suitable for the mission and also
                    because of the holiday season.<note n="83" xml:id="d124fn83">The departure of
                        the mission was postponed successively until February 1924.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodge</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
